doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    title Are we (I)DE yet?
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="style.css")
    meta(charset="utf-8")
  body
    .container
      header
        h1 Are we (I)DE yet?
        p An overview about the state of Rust development environments and their integrated bretheren.
        p.beta This overview is so much beta, it's likely that I have forgotten many things!

      section
        h1 Text Editors

        ul
          li
            h2 Atom
            p
              | The package 
              a(href="https://atom.io/packages/language-rust") language-rust
              |  brings
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
              li code snippets
            p
              | With 
              a(href="https://atom.io/packages/linter-rust") linter-rust
              |  (which relies on 
              a(href="https://atom.io/packages/linter") linter
              | ) you get
            ul.features
              li linter
            p
              | Racer integration via 
              a(href="https://atom.io/packages/racer") racer
              |  brings
            ul.features
              li code completion


          li
            h2 Emacs
            p
              | For Emacs there is 
              a(href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-mode") RustMode
              |  installable from source or via MELPA, it brings
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
              li snippets
            p With 
              a(href="https://github.com/flycheck/flycheck-rust") Flycheck
              |  comes
            ul.features
              li syntax checking
            p
              a(href="https://github.com/phildawes/racer") Racer
              |  gets you
            ul.features
              li code completion

          li
            h2 Geany
            p Without further trouble Geany brings
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
              li build scripts (Cargo support coming soon)

          li
            h2 Kate
            p Kate has included
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
            p
              | With some help of 
              a(href="https://github.com/phildawes/racer") Racer
              |  you get
            ul.features
              li code completion

          li
            h2 Sublime Text 2/3
            p
              a(href="https://packagecontrol.io/packages/Rust") Rust Package
              |  brings 
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
              li snippets
              li build scripts
            p
              a(href="https://packagecontrol.io/packages/RustAutoComplete") RustAutoComplete
              |  uses Racer to bring
            ul.features
              li code completion 
          li
            h2 Vim
            p
              a(href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust.vim") rust.vim
              |  offers
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
            p
              | With 
              a(href="https://github.com/phildawes/racer") Racer
              |  you get
            ul.features
              li code completion
              li goto definition

      section
        h1 Integrated Development Environments

        ul
          li
            h2 Eclipse
            p
              | The plugin 
              a(href="https://rustdt.github.io") RustDT
              |  works best when Racer is installed and then offers
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
              li snippets
              li project wizard
              li goto definition
              li gdb debugging
          li
            h2 IntelliJ IDEA
            p
              | The 
              a(href="https://github.com/Vektah/idea-rust") Rust plugin
              |  is a bit outdated.
          li
            h2 Visual Studio
            p
              | With  
              a(href="https://github.com/PistonDevelopers/VisualRust") Visual Rust
              |  you get
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
              li project support
              li build scripts
          li
            h2 SolidOak
            p
              a(href="https://sekao.net/solidoak/") SolidOak
              |  is the first Rust-specific IDE.
              |  It has integrated
            ul.features
              li syntax highlighting
              li code completion
            p
              |  It wraps Cargo instructions for creating, building, testing and running projects.

      section
        h1 Meta

        ul
          li
            h2 Racer
            p
              a(href="https://github.com/phildawes/racer") Racer
              |  is a code completion tool for Rust that is developed standalone.
              |  It is the basis for code completion in pretty much every setup.

      footer
        ul
          li
            p
              | Background:
              br
              a(href="http://subtlepatterns.com/sprinkles/") Sprinkles
          li
            p
              | Inspiration:
              br
              a(href="http://arewewebyet.com/") Are we web yet?
          li
